OL,3,CMan from Nottingham blames health
OL,4,Cservices for his brother's death
OL,6,FAfter he was discharged, he repeatedly
OL,7,Fphoned 999 and 111 as his symptoms
OL,8,Fworsened, but was told it wasn't
OL,9,Fserious enough to need an ambulance.
OL,11,FDuring the calls between 12 and 15
OL,12,FMay, he complained of vomiting, pain,
OL,13,Fdizziness and blood in his urine
OL,14,Fbefore his hospital admission.
OL,16,FAt the inquest, Adam's family were
OL,17,Ftold that had things been done
OL,18,Fdifferently, he would have most likely
OL,19,Fsurvived.
